      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/126/5549",
      "text": [
        " : \"مَرِضَ عَلِيُّ بْنُ اَلْحُسَيْنِ عَلَيْهِمَا اَلسَّلاَمُ ثَلاَثَ مَرَضَاتٍ فِي كُلِّ مَرْضَةٍ يُوصِي بِوَصِيَّةٍ فَإِذَا أَفَاقَ أَمْضَى وَصِيَّتَهُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5549 - Al-Hasan ibn Ali Al-Washa' narrated from Abdullah ibn Sinan from Umar ibn Yazid from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"Imam Ali ibn Al-Hussain (as), fell ill three times, and in each illness, he would make a will. When he recovered, he would carry out his will.\""
        ]
      }
